qFallbackTitle.desc:
Corresponds to the label of the dimension that is selected.
If the label is not defined then the field name is used.

qApprMaxGlyphCount.desc: Length of the longest value in the field.

qLocked.desc: Is set to true if the field is locked.

qSortIndicator.desc:
Sort indicator.
This parameter is optional.
The default value is no sorting.

qGroupFallbackTitles.desc:
Array of dimension labels.
Contains the labels of all dimensions in a hierarchy group (for example the labels of all dimensions in a drill down group).

qGroupPos.desc:
Index of the dimension that is currently in use.
qGroupPos is set to 0 if there are no hierarchical groups (drill-down groups) or cycle groups.

qStateCounts.desc: Number of values in a particular state.

qTags.desc:
Gives information on a field. For example, it can return the type of the field.
Examples: key, text, ASCII

qError.desc:
This parameter is optional.
Gives information on the error.

qReverseSort.desc: If set to true, it inverts the sort criteria in the field.

qIsSemantic.desc: If set to true, it means that the field is a semantic.

qNumFormat.desc:
Format of the field.
This parameter is optional.

qIsAutoFormat.desc: This parameter is set to true if qNumFormat is set to U (unknown). The engine guesses the type of the field based on the field's definition.

qDerivedField.desc: Is derived field is used as a dimension.
